's _really_ only valid as a bitmask.<br /><br />So I think we're better off reverting that ordering change, and testing <br />the bitmap properly.<br /><br />&gt; Any tests using &lt; TASK_STOPPED or the like are left over from the time when<br />&gt; the TASK_ZOMBIE and TASK_DEAD bits were in the same word, and it served to<br />&gt; check for "stopped or dead".<br /><br />Correct again.<br /><br />Btw, that brings up another thing: those EXIT_ZOMBIE/EXIT_DEAD flags are <br />really really confusing. <br /><br />It's two different words, but the way we use them in get_task_state(), <br />they are or'ed together, which is why they need to have non-overlapping <br />bit definitions. But there's no comment about that anywhere.<br /><br />I'll add a comment to &lt;linux/sched.h&gt; about it.<br /><br />Thanks,<br /><br />		Linus<br />-<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.kernel.org<br />More majordomo info at  <a href="http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html">http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html</a><br />Please read the FAQ at  <a href="http://www.tux.org/lkml/">http://www.tux.org/lkml/</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
